News24Constitutional court. (News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - President Jacob Zuma has started consulting political parties on the appointment of a Constitutional Court judge, the Presidency has said.Zuma has written to party leaders represented in the National Assembly, telling them of his intention to appoint a Constitutional Court judge.This follows a rigorous interview process of candidates by the Judicial Service Commission.The JSC then submitted names for Zuma to consider, and he is in the process of doing so, the Presidency said on Tuesday.Earlier this month, JSC member Thoko Didiza said that, following interviews, they would recommend four candidates to Zuma:24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.